					<Quiz questions={empty} 
						shortAnswerQuestions={[
							{
								question: "As demonstrated in the image above, is there a higher or lower chance of death for black moms and their infants as opposed to white moms? Why do you think this is?",
							}]}
						 />
				</div>
				<p>Another possible outcome is stillbirth, where the baby dies in the mother's womb.</p>
				<p>Black women in America are over twice as likely to have a stillbirth when compared to white women, and this is often because physicians often dismiss the concerns of Black women, who often have complications that could lead to severe consequences with the pregnancy and the baby eventually dying as a result (Eldeib and Hager). </p>
				<div class="quiz-section">
				<Quiz questions={empty} 
					shortAnswerQuestions={[
						{
								question: "What effects could a stillbirth have on a mother and their family?",
						}]}
					/>
				</div>
				<p>These are things that Aaliyah could have gone through because of the dismissal of her concerns.</p>
				<p>Now, see what would have happened if Aaliyah chose to go to a Black female doctor who takes her concerns seriously.</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}


	{pageNumber === 9 && (
		<>
			<h2>After visit with black doctor</h2>
			<div class="content">
				<p>Aaliyah decided to get a second opinion, she reached out to a family friend and they recommended a local black doctor. </p>
				<p>	Aaliyah: “Hi, my name is Aaliyah, I am 30 weeks pregnant, I have been experiencing a lot of symptoms, and am unsure of what it is - they are progressively getting worse.” </p>
				<p>Doctor: “Can you list out your symptoms for me?” </p>
				<p>Aaliyah: “I’ve developed blurry vision, shortness or breath, abdominal pain, headaches and am very tired. I am just concerned for the health of myself and my baby. I have tried talking to another doctor about this, but was dismissed without any proper care or guidance. ” </p>
				<p>Doctor: “Oh no! I am so sorry about your other doctor not taking you seriously! This sounds like a case of preeclampsia, we can test this with a simple blood test, urine test, and ultrasound to check the size of the baby.”</p>
				<h3>Doctor diagnosed Aaliyah with Preeclampsia</h3>
				<p>Press the button to explore possible treatments.</p>
			</div>
		</>
	)}

